    "name": "term_loan_b_5y_floating",
    "domain": "fixed_income.term_loan",
    "description": "Synthetic USD term loan B 5Y floating-rate facility with quarterly amortization. Two-step calibration: USD-OIS bootstrapped from synthetic SOFR OIS quotes, USD-SOFR-3M bootstrapped from synthetic 3M-Term-SOFR IRS quotes against the calibrated discount curve. The instrument's primary discount curve (USD-CORP), credit curve (ACME-HZD), and the auxiliary curves (USD-TREASURY, HYCO-HZD) are preserved verbatim in initial_market. Self-test contract: re-running calibration + pricing must reproduce the recorded values within solver tolerance.",
    "valuation_date": "2026-04-30",
    "source": "formula",
    "source_detail": "Finstack Quant canonical fixed-income pricing calculation on deterministic synthetic market inputs Phase-2 envelope migration (2026-05-09): replaced the materialized USD-OIS and USD-SOFR-3M curves with a two-step calibration plan (POC #4 pattern from market-bootstrap-phase-5 plan §16). Other curves (USD-CORP, USD-TREASURY, ACME-HZD, HYCO-HZD) remain materialized in initial_market. Expected outputs recaptured from Finstack itself; the original synthetic-curve test contract is replaced by a self-test contract: bit-stable round-trip through calibrate + price. Re-blessed 2026-05-30: term-loan CS01 now reports the market-standard z-spread bump instead of 0.0. The discounting pricer never consumes the hazard curve, so the canonical par-spread/hazard CS01 was identically zero for loans; CS01 is now computed by solving the z-spread to the quoted clean price and bumping +/-1bp (see metrics::sensitivities::cs01_z_spread). Old: cs01=0.0. New: cs01=-8112.699659444392 (negative = long credit risk; larger magnitude than the floating-rate DV01 because the z-spread shift hits discounting on all flows including principal, whereas DV01 largely offsets via floating-coupon reprojection).",
    "captured_by": "jeickmeier",
    "captured_on": "2026-05-01",
    "last_reviewed_by": "jeickmeier",
    "last_reviewed_on": "2026-05-30",
